Needed for distribution, but does not build anything -- packages pre-built files
Roy Platon (Orig).  MJC will review this code.  Clive has SUN, Vito has source.

column2: Name: Package name.  Where a package is in CVS, this is its `component' name
Status: S=supported, U=unsupported, X=to be reassigned, J=supported by JAC
CVS status: yes=in CVS; obsolete=in the obsolete tree; thirdparty=in the thirdparty tree; java=this is a java package name, rather than a component name
Maintainer: A contact name.  Components which are in CVS should have a <role>owner</role> element in their component.xml
indicating the owner/maintainer, and no entry in this column
Copyright: the copyright owner(s).  Where this is CLRC, the licence will be GPL
